Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:05.73,English,,0,0,0,,It is a capped column.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:05.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.73,0:05:07.95,English,,0,0,0,,It started out growing as a column,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.73,0:05:07.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:09.44,English,,0,0,0,,but then the temperature changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:09.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.44,0:05:12.04,English,,0,0,0,,and then you've got plates growing on either end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.44,0:05:12.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.35,0:05:20.64,English,,0,0,0,,It's just a cacophony of different shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.35,0:05:20.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.64,0:05:22.61,English,,0,0,0,,All of these appear spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.64,0:05:22.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:25.36,English,,0,0,0,,There's no DNA or any kind of a blueprint
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:25.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:26.19,English,,0,0,0,,for what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:26.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.19,0:05:28.55,English,,0,0,0,,It's just water vapor freezing into ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.19,0:05:28.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:29.53,English,,0,0,0,,and all this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:29.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:31.13,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] So you've identified
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:31.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.13,0:05:34.25,English,,0,0,0,,35 different types of snowflakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.13,0:05:34.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.25,0:05:36.77,English,,0,0,0,,- Yes, there's no really one way
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.25,0:05:36.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:39.57,English,,0,0,0,,to define a type of snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:39.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.57,0:05:42.76,English,,0,0,0,,The first chart of snowflakes is like 41, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.57,0:05:42.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.76,0:05:45.48,English,,0,0,0,,and then it got bigger - 60 or 70,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.76,0:05:45.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.48,0:05:48.80,English,,0,0,0,,and the latest one by some Japanese physicists,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.48,0:05:48.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:52.46,English,,0,0,0,,I think had 108 different types of snowflakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:52.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.46,0:05:54.95,English,,0,0,0,,and I found 108 was too many.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.46,0:05:54.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.44,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] How does simple ice create so many distinct forms?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,平平无奇的冰为何能产生变化万千的形态呢
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:07.67,English,,0,0,0,,All snowflakes form in much the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:07.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,各种雪花生成的方式基本相同
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.67,0:06:10.03,English,,0,0,0,,Water evaporates into water vapor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.67,0:06:10.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,水蒸发形成水蒸气
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.03,0:06:13.04,English,,0,0,0,,individual molecules bouncing around in the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.03,0:06:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,孤立的分子在大气中弹跳
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.04,0:06:14.66,English,,0,0,0,,and as this vapor rises,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.04,0:06:14.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着蒸气上升
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.66,0:06:17.69,English,,0,0,0,,it cools and becomes super saturated,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.66,0:06:17.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些分子冷却并转变成过饱和状态
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:20.11,English,,0,0,0,,meaning there are more water molecules in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:20.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,意味着这时空气中的水分子的数量多于
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.11,0:06:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,than there would be in equilibrium at this temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.11,0:06:23.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相同温度下平衡状态的水分子数量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:26.24,English,,0,0,0,,Water molecules condense onto dust particles
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:26.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,水分子在尘埃颗粒上凝聚
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,to form tiny droplets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:28.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生微小的水滴
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.26,0:06:30.85,English,,0,0,0,,And although the temperature may be below freezing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.26,0:06:30.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管环境温度可能低于水的凝固点
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.85,0:06:33.83,English,,0,0,0,,the droplets don't immediately freeze,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.85,0:06:33.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些水滴不会立即冻结
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:37.90,English,,0,0,0,,but at some point, one droplet will freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:37.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是在某个位置  一滴水可能会冷凝
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.90,0:06:41.38,English,,0,0,0,,Inside, the water molecules lock into place,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.90,0:06:41.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,微观上  其中的水分子被固定在位置上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:44.46,English,,0,0,0,,forming a hexagonal crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:44.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形成一个六方晶体
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.46,0:06:48.58,English,,0,0,0,,This structure results from the peculiarities of water molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.46,0:06:48.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种结构源自水分子的特性
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.58,0:06:51.95,English,,0,0,0,,Oxygen atoms attract electrons more than hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.58,0:06:51.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氧原子吸引电子的能力比氢原子强
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.95,0:06:54.47,English,,0,0,0,,And since the molecule has a bent shape,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.95,0:06:54.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又因为水分子本身成V形
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.47,0:06:57.60,English,,0,0,0,,it's polar with oxygen being slightly negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.47,0:06:57.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以会极化  在氧原子一端略带负电
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.60,0:07:00.22,English,,0,0,0,,and the hydrogens, slightly positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.60,0:07:00.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氢原子一端则略带正电
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.22,0:07:04.03,English,,0,0,0,,Since unlike charges attract, hydrogen from one molecule
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.22,0:07:04.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由于异号电荷相吸引  一个水分子中的氢原子
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.03,0:07:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,will sit next to an oxygen from another molecule,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.03,0:07:07.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会靠近另一个水分子中的氧原子
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.00,0:07:09.77,English,,0,0,0,,forming a so-called hydrogen bond,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.00,0:07:09.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生所谓的氢键
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.77,0:07:13.33,English,,0,0,0,,and this is what creates the hexagonal molecular lattice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.77,0:07:13.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正是这种相互作用  让分子形成了六边形的晶格
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.40,0:07:16.50,English,,0,0,0,,But how does this microscopic lattice
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.40,0:07:16.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这样的微观晶格
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.50,0:07:20.15,English,,0,0,0,,grow into a hexagonal crystal that we can see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.50,0:07:20.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是如何生长为我们所见的六方晶体的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:23.46,English,,0,0,0,,- So you start with a chunk of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:23.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,假定起初有一小块冰晶
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:26.63,English,,0,0,0,,and these little guys are meant to be water molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:26.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些小家伙就代表水分子
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:29.37,English,,0,0,0,,And what happens is there are these flat surfaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.37,0:07:30.76,English,,0,0,0,,which are the facet surfaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:30.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在  看这些平坦的界面（即晶体的刻面）
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:34.56,English,,0,0,0,,and at a molecular scale, they're very smooth and flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:34.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在分子尺度上  它们非常光滑、平整
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:36.68,English,,0,0,0,,And so when a molecule hits,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:36.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当一个分子撞上去
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:39.73,English,,0,0,0,,a water vapor molecule hits that smooth and flat surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:39.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个水蒸气分子  撞击这个平整而光滑的界面时
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:41.00,English,,0,0,0,,it tends to bounce off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:41.00,English,,0,0,0,,它会被反弹
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.00,0:07:43.07,English,,0,0,0,,Whereas here, it's rough,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.00,0:07:43.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这些地方较为粗糙
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.07,0:07:45.77,English,,0,0,0,,there are a lot of dangling molecular bonds over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.07,0:07:45.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以会有很多自由分子在那里成键
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:46.71,English,,0,0,0,,That's a rough surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:46.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是个粗糙的界面
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:50.02,English,,0,0,0,,And so when these molecules hit, they tend to stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:50.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以如果分子撞击晶体 它们更倾向凝结在此处
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,It's a statistical thing, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:51.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这当然是统计意义上的结论
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.96,0:07:54.38,English,,0,0,0,,but the probabilities are high that they stick here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.96,0:07:54.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但分子固定在这里的概率较高
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.38,0:07:56.14,English,,0,0,0,,and low that they stick here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.38,0:07:56.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而固定在这里的概率较低
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:58.77,English,,0,0,0,,So if you take any shape, and you just let it grow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:58.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以  如果随便选一种形状的冰晶  任其生长
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.77,0:08:02.09,English,,0,0,0,,for a little while, the rough areas fill in,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.77,0:08:02.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只要一小会儿  这些崎岖的位置就会被填满
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.09,0:08:04.55,English,,0,0,0,,and the flat areas don't grow very fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.09,0:08:04.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而平坦的位置不会生长太快
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:06.42,English,,0,0,0,,and you end up with a faceted shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:06.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样最终就得到了一个多面体的形状
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.58,0:08:10.09,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] And that's how we get from the quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.58,0:08:10.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们根据量子力学推演出了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.09,0:08:15.09,English,,0,0,0,,that governs a water molecule, to a hexagonal prism of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.09,0:08:15.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个水分子如何变为六棱柱形状的冰
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.24,0:08:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,This prism has two basal facets and six prism facets,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.24,0:08:20.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,六棱柱有两个底面和六个侧面
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:21.73,English,,0,0,0,,which is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:21.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:24.96,English,,0,0,0,,If the basal facets grow fast, you get a column.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:24.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果底面长得快  就会得到柱状的雪花
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.96,0:08:28.93,English,,0,0,0,,If the prism facets grow faster, you get a flat snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.96,0:08:28.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果棱柱的侧面生长更快  则会得到片状的雪花
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.06,0:08:31.93,English,,0,0,0,,Once there is a seed crystal,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.06,0:08:31.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一旦某处有一个晶种
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.93,0:08:34.43,English,,0,0,0,,nearby water droplets evaporate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.93,0:08:34.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,附近的液滴将蒸发产生水蒸气分子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.43,0:08:38.77,English,,0,0,0,,and deposit water molecules onto the growing snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.43,0:08:38.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些分子会再度凝结在生长中的雪花上
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.77,0:08:43.77,English,,0,0,0,,Since the corners of the hexagonal prism stick out farther into humid air,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.77,0:08:43.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由于六方晶体的棱角与潮湿空气接触更充分
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:45.31,English,,0,0,0,,they grow faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:45.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们生长得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.31,0:08:48.31,English,,0,0,0,,and now they extend even farther,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.31,0:08:48.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在它们以伸展到更远处
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:52.27,English,,0,0,0,,so they grow even faster in a positive feedback loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:52.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种正反馈机制使得它们生长得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.27,0:08:55.99,English,,0,0,0,,This gives rise to six radial branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.27,0:08:55.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由此就产生了辐射状的六簇分支
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:58.31,English,,0,0,0,,At the corners of these branches,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:58.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这些分支的棱角上
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.31,0:09:01.60,English,,0,0,0,,additional branches can form for the same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.31,0:09:01.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,新的分支也会基于相同的原理生成
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:05.12,English,,0,0,0,,Around a hundred thousand droplets are required
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:05.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约需要十万滴水
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.12,0:09:07.05,English,,0,0,0,,to make a single snowflake,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.12,0:09:07.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,才能产生一片雪花
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.05,0:09:10.45,English,,0,0,0,,and the process usually takes 30 to 45 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.05,0:09:10.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,整个过程会经过大约 30 到 45 分钟
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.93,0:09:14.17,English,,0,0,0,,In the 1930s, Ukichiro Nakaya
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.93,0:09:14.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:16.27,English,,0,0,0,,was systematically studying snowflakes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:16.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.27,0:09:18.91,English,,0,0,0,,at the University of Hokkaido in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.27,0:09:18.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:21.79,English,,0,0,0,,He discovered that the different types of snowflakes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:21.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:25.52,English,,0,0,0,,don't all occur under the same conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:25.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:27.32,English,,0,0,0,,Instead, two factors,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:27.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.32,0:09:30.38,English,,0,0,0,,the temperature and level of super saturation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.32,0:09:30.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:33.40,English,,0,0,0,,determine what type of snowflake grows.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:33.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.40,0:09:37.46,English,,0,0,0,,His findings are summarized in the Nakaya Diagram,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.40,0:09:37.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.46,0:09:40.07,English,,0,0,0,,but it's not a simple pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.46,0:09:40.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.07,0:09:43.39,English,,0,0,0,,Around -2 Celsius, you get plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.07,0:09:43.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:47.26,English,,0,0,0,,At -5 Celsius, columns and needles form.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:47.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.26,0:09:50.44,English,,0,0,0,,At -15 Celsius, it's plates again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.26,0:09:50.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.44,0:09:54.69,English,,0,0,0,,and then below -20, you get columns and plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.44,0:09:54.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.69,English,,0,0,0,,The Nakaya Diagram allows us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.69,0:10:00.36,English,,0,0,0,,to understand a rough history of any snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.69,0:10:00.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.36,0:10:05.36,English,,0,0,0,,Does each snowflake in essence reveal its history
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.36,0:10:05.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:07.90,English,,0,0,0,,through its shape?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:07.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:10.27,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, absolutely, to some degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:10.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.27,0:10:12.11,English,,0,0,0,,You can definitely look at a snowflake and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.27,0:10:12.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.11,0:10:13.94,English,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, I know what conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.11,0:10:13.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.94,0:10:16.56,English,,0,0,0,,"that crystal grew under, more or less."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.94,0:10:16.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:19.39,English,,0,0,0,,Your typical weather patterns, fronts, cold front,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:19.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:20.87,English,,0,0,0,,that produces a lot of capped columns,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:20.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.87,0:10:23.35,English,,0,0,0,,because as the cloud moves up, it starts to get colder
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.87,0:10:23.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:28.35,English,,0,0,0,,and initially start to freeze at around -6, -10.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:28.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.49,0:10:30.82,English,,0,0,0,,That makes columns, and as it gets colder,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.49,0:10:30.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.82,0:10:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,then it makes branches and plates,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.82,0:10:33.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.16,0:10:35.61,English,,0,0,0,,and so you get capped columns.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.16,0:10:35.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:36.89,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] This also explains
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:36.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.89,0:10:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,why snowflakes are so intricate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.89,0:10:39.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.12,0:10:42.31,English,,0,0,0,,The temperature and humidity at each moment of growth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.12,0:10:42.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:45.35,English,,0,0,0,,determines the structures formed in that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:45.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:48.58,English,,0,0,0,,The symmetry you see is not because one side
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:48.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:51.28,English,,0,0,0,,somehow knows what the other side is doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:51.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.28,0:10:53.97,English,,0,0,0,,but because both sides of a single snowflake grow
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.28,0:10:53.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:56.30,English,,0,0,0,,in the exact same conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:56.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.30,0:10:59.30,English,,0,0,0,,- When the crystal changes its position,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.30,0:10:59.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:00.83,English,,0,0,0,,the temperature will change, say,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:00.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.83,0:11:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,and all six branches will see the same temperature change,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.83,0:11:04.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.48,0:11:06.60,English,,0,0,0,,and so they'll all respond the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.48,0:11:06.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:10.38,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Different snowflakes, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:10.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.38,0:11:12.37,English,,0,0,0,,each take a unique path,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.38,0:11:12.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:15.65,English,,0,0,0,,and therefore they experience a unique set of conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:15.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.65,0:11:18.52,English,,0,0,0,,which is why no two snowflakes are alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.65,0:11:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.89,0:11:23.33,English,,0,0,0,,But in the lab, you can carefully control the conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.89,0:11:23.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在这个实验中  你可以精细地控制条件
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.33,0:11:25.41,English,,0,0,0,,so theoretically it should be possible
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.33,0:11:25.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以理论上说
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:28.41,English,,0,0,0,,to create almost identical snowflakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:28.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,制造几乎一模一样的雪花是有可能的 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:30.41,English,,0,0,0,,and indeed, Ken has.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:30.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上  Ken确实可以
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:32.15,English,,0,0,0,,What's in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:32.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里面是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.15,0:11:34.60,English,,0,0,0,,- Poke your flashlight in there, and you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.15,0:11:34.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把手电筒伸进去  你会看见的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.60,0:11:37.96,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Ah ha, I'm imagining these are seed crystals of a sort?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.60,0:11:37.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,啊哈  我想这些是某种晶种吧
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.40,English,,0,0,0,,- [Ken] Those are a little sparkly snow crystals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一些发光的雪晶
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.40,0:11:41.23,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.40,0:11:41.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哦
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.23,0:11:42.61,English,,0,0,0,,- You know this is another little chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.23,0:11:42.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是另一种意义上的小房间
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:43.97,English,,0,0,0,,It's just a cold plate,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:43.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一个冷却台
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:47.00,English,,0,0,0,,and there's a little sapphire disc in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:47.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里面有一张小蓝宝石碟片
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.00,0:11:49.32,English,,0,0,0,,and then I'm going to push this thing, my sapphire,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.00,0:11:49.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后我要把我的蓝宝石推进去
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.32,0:11:52.57,English,,0,0,0,,all the way in here, and the crystals will waft onto to it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.32,0:11:52.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些晶体就会飘到上面去
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.57,0:11:54.31,English,,0,0,0,,and hopefully stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.57,0:11:54.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大概率它们会待在这
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.26,0:11:56.49,English,,0,0,0,,The idea popped in, it's like,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.26,0:11:56.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个想法大概是这样出现的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.49,0:11:58.09,English,,0,0,0,,oh, if I grow two next to one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.49,0:11:58.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我把两片雪花放在相邻的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:11:59.86,English,,0,0,0,,they'll be kind of identical,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:11:59.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们就会有点类似
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.86,0:12:02.47,English,,0,0,0,,and I call them identical twin snowflakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.86,0:12:02.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我把它们称为同卵双胞胎雪花
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.47,0:12:04.56,English,,0,0,0,,'cause they're like identical twin people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.47,0:12:04.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它们就像是同卵双胞胎
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.56,0:12:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,They're not exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.56,0:12:06.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们并不是完全一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.04,0:12:09.14,English,,0,0,0,,but clearly more alike than you would ever expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.04,0:12:09.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但很显然比你预期的要相似很多
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:19.67,English,,0,0,0,,Is it really true that no two snowflakes are alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:19.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有两片雪花是相似的  这句话真的是对的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.24,English,,0,0,0,,You know, that's just a silly question.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你也知道这问题挺愚蠢的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:25.90,English,,0,0,0,,It's silly because no two trees are like,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:25.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为没有两棵一模一样的树
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:29.39,English,,0,0,0,,no two grains of sand are like, no two anything are alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:29.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有两粒一样的沙  没有两个事物是一模一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:31.51,English,,0,0,0,,Anything that has any complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:31.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只要某个事物存在复杂性
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:33.17,English,,0,0,0,,is different from everything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:33.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就会与其他事物不同
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.17,0:12:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,because once you introduce complexity,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.17,0:12:36.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为一旦涉及到复杂性
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:40.25,English,,0,0,0,,then there's just an uncountable number of ways to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:40.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,创造这项事物的途径就不可胜数
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:41.90,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] If a pair of twins snowflakes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:41.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果一对“双胞胎”雪花
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:43.87,English,,0,0,0,,are growing too close together,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:43.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生长的地方特别近
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.87,0:12:46.89,English,,0,0,0,,they end up competing for moisture between them,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.87,0:12:46.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们会竞争二者间的水分
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.89,0:12:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,stunting both of their growths.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.89,0:12:49.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最终同时阻碍了它们的生长
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:53.41,English,,0,0,0,,The Nakaya Diagram allows us to understand a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:53.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中谷图表可以让我们
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:55.24,English,,0,0,0,,about snowflake formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:55.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更好地理解雪花的形成
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.24,0:12:56.75,English,,0,0,0,,Ken has used his experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.24,0:12:56.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Ken通过自己的实验
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.75,0:12:59.16,English,,0,0,0,,to build his own version of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.75,0:12:59.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,建立了他自己的图表
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:00.84,English,,0,0,0,,But what it doesn't explain
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:00.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这并没有解释
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:04.29,English,,0,0,0,,is why do ice crystals form this way in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:04.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么冰晶最初是这样形成的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.29,0:13:07.45,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, why do we get plates and then columns
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.29,0:13:07.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是  为什么会先产生片状的雪花  然后是柱状

Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:10.42,English,,0,0,0,,and then plates and columns again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:10.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,之后又是片状  最后又是柱状
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.42,0:13:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,This has been a mystery,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.42,0:13:11.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这早就是一个谜团了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.92,0:13:16.30,English,,0,0,0,,essentially since Nakaya introduced his diagram back in the 1930s,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.92,0:13:16.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以追溯到上世纪30年代  提出中谷图表的时候

Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.30,0:13:19.14,English,,0,0,0,,but Ken believes he now has an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.30,0:13:19.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过Ken相信  他已得到答案了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.14,0:13:20.82,English,,0,0,0,,Anytime you have a crystal,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.14,0:13:20.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,假设你有一个（单）晶体
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.82,0:13:24.42,English,,0,0,0,,the reason why you get these smooth flat facets
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.82,0:13:24.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它之所以有光滑平整的切面
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.42,0:13:28.09,English,,0,0,0,,is because it's not easy to grow more crystal on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.42,0:13:28.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是因为顶面很难继续生长晶体了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.09,0:13:30.88,English,,0,0,0,,There are so-called nucleation barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.09,0:13:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是所谓的成核势垒
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.88,0:13:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,What you need is a critical density of additional molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.88,0:13:33.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你需要知道这种物质的其他分子的临界密度
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.80,0:13:36.11,English,,0,0,0,,of the substance before they can come together
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.80,0:13:36.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,达到临界密度后它们会聚集在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.11,0:13:39.64,English,,0,0,0,,to form a little island that is stable enough to grow
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.11,0:13:39.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形成一个足够稳定的小岛
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.64,0:13:42.40,English,,0,0,0,,and add another layer onto the crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.64,0:13:42.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并叠加在晶体上面
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:44.42,English,,0,0,0,,When you're first forming a snowflake,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:44.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一次生成雪花时
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:46.98,English,,0,0,0,,you're always gonna start with a hexagonal prism
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:46.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你总是会从一个六角棱柱开始
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:48.81,English,,0,0,0,,with its two basal facets
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:48.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它有两个底面
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:51.31,English,,0,0,0,,and six prism facets around the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:51.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和六个侧面
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.31,0:13:53.97,English,,0,0,0,,And the nucleation barrier for the basal facets
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.31,0:13:53.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,底面的成核势垒
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:56.98,English,,0,0,0,,is different than that of the prism facets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:56.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与侧面的成核势垒是不同的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:13:59.77,English,,0,0,0,,If the nucleation barrier is lower for the prism facets,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:13:59.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果侧面的成核势垒比较低
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:03.22,English,,0,0,0,,then they grow faster, and you get plate like structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:03.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,侧面就会生长得更快  最终得到片状结构
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.22,0:14:05.82,English,,0,0,0,,If the nucleation barrier is lower for the basal facets,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.22,0:14:05.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果底面的成核势垒比较低
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,then they grow faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:07.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,底面就会生长得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:09.61,English,,0,0,0,,and you end up with column-like structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:09.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最终得到柱状结构
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.61,0:14:11.69,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the nucleation barriers of ice
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.61,0:14:11.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:14.24,English,,0,0,0,,are known as a function of temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:14.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:17.43,English,,0,0,0,,and this explains why around -2,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:17.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.43,0:14:20.16,English,,0,0,0,,the prism facets grow faster, and you get plates,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.43,0:14:20.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.16,0:14:23.24,English,,0,0,0,,because their nucleation barrier is lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.16,0:14:23.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.24,0:14:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,You can also see why below -20 or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.24,0:14:26.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.06,0:14:27.79,English,,0,0,0,,well then you get columns,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.06,0:14:27.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.79,0:14:30.73,English,,0,0,0,,because the basal facet nucleation barrier is lower
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.79,0:14:30.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.73,0:14:32.33,English,,0,0,0,,at those temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.73,0:14:32.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.33,0:14:35.37,English,,0,0,0,,But what doesn't make sense is why we should get columns
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.33,0:14:35.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.37,0:14:39.67,English,,0,0,0,,at around -5 Celsius and then plates again at -15.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.37,0:14:39.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.50,0:14:42.56,English,,0,0,0,,So what is happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.50,0:14:42.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:45.58,English,,0,0,0,,Well Ken's hypothesis is that these nucleation barriers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:45.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.58,0:14:48.44,English,,0,0,0,,are valid only for large flat facets,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.58,0:14:48.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:50.64,English,,0,0,0,,but if you had really narrow facets,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:50.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.64,0:14:53.05,English,,0,0,0,,well, the nucleation barriers would be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.64,0:14:53.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:55.81,English,,0,0,0,,So Ken proposes that narrow basal facets
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:55.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:59.69,English,,0,0,0,,have a dip in their nucleation barrier around -4 Celsius,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:59.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.69,0:15:03.15,English,,0,0,0,,and narrow prism facets have a dip at -15,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.69,0:15:03.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.15,0:15:06.99,English,,0,0,0,,so his hypothesis is that the graph should look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.15,0:15:06.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,This then is consistent with all the different forms
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:09.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:12.38,English,,0,0,0,,of snowflakes that grow at different temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:12.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.38,0:15:14.99,English,,0,0,0,,But what accounts for these dips?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.38,0:15:14.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.99,0:15:17.70,English,,0,0,0,,Well, let's say we have a narrow prism facet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.99,0:15:17.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:20.34,English,,0,0,0,,so we're growing a plate snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:20.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.34,0:15:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,Water molecules that hit the basal facets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.34,0:15:22.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.96,0:15:25.28,English,,0,0,0,,are unlikely to reach the critical density required
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.96,0:15:25.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.28,0:15:27.36,English,,0,0,0,,to overcome the nucleation barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.28,0:15:27.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.36,0:15:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,so that surface grows only slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.36,0:15:30.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.14,0:15:33.27,English,,0,0,0,,But on either side of this narrow prism facet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.14,0:15:33.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.27,0:15:36.40,English,,0,0,0,,water molecules can stick on the rough edges,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.27,0:15:36.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.40,0:15:38.15,English,,0,0,0,,and to minimize surface energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.40,0:15:38.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.15,0:15:41.98,English,,0,0,0,,the ideal shape of this face would be semicircular.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.15,0:15:41.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.98,0:15:45.59,English,,0,0,0,,But if only the top few layers of water molecules are mobile
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.98,0:15:45.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.59,0:15:47.48,English,,0,0,0,,to try to lower the surface energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.59,0:15:47.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:50.45,English,,0,0,0,,many of them diffuse onto the prism facet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:50.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:51.43,English,,0,0,0,,and in the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:51.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:53.36,English,,0,0,0,,they exceed the critical density required
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.36,0:15:55.37,English,,0,0,0,,to overcome the nucleation barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.36,0:15:55.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:15:58.89,English,,0,0,0,,and so they can grow the crystal on the prism facet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:15:58.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:01.60,English,,0,0,0,,So due to this narrow edge, the nucleation barrier
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:01.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.60,0:16:03.77,English,,0,0,0,,is effectively lower than it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.60,0:16:03.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.77,0:16:06.35,English,,0,0,0,,for a large prism facet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.77,0:16:06.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.35,0:16:08.70,English,,0,0,0,,A similar effect happens for the basal facets,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.35,0:16:08.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.70,0:16:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,just at a different temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.70,0:16:10.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.72,0:16:13.11,English,,0,0,0,,And Ken has done experiments to investigate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.72,0:16:13.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:16.20,English,,0,0,0,,whether these effects are observed in the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:16.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:19.28,English,,0,0,0,,- And so I did a series of experiments using that apparatus
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:19.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.28,0:16:21.97,English,,0,0,0,,and man, it's just like, boom, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.28,0:16:21.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:23.60,English,,0,0,0,, Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:23.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.68,0:16:26.83,English,,0,0,0,,When you make a model,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.68,0:16:26.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.83,0:16:29.34,English,,0,0,0,,and you sort of find it's supposed to do something,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.83,0:16:29.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:33.88,English,,0,0,0,,and it sorta does, it's just like, this might be right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:33.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.88,0:16:37.38,English,,0,0,0,,- So far, the results agree nicely with the hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.88,0:16:37.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.38,0:16:40.78,English,,0,0,0,,So after 85 years, maybe we now understand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.38,0:16:40.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.78,0:16:42.82,English,,0,0,0,,the molecular physics of ice well enough
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.78,0:16:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.82,0:16:45.54,English,,0,0,0,,to finally explain why snowflakes grow
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.82,0:16:45.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:47.28,English,,0,0,0,,into such a diverse collection
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:47.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.28,0:16:50.65,English,,0,0,0,,of columnar and plate-like forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.28,0:16:50.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:52.30,English,,0,0,0,,- And I've done a lot of my career
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:52.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.30,0:16:55.13,English,,0,0,0,,in astronomy and astrophysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.30,0:16:55.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.13,0:16:57.77,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever asks you what it's good for, I mean, never.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.13,0:16:57.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.77,0:16:59.34,English,,0,0,0,,Not even once did anyone say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.77,0:16:59.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,"What are those black holes gonna be used for?" No,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:02.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:06.84,English,,0,0,0,,Saturn's rings, "Why do you care about Saturn's rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:06.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.84,0:17:09.11,English,,0,0,0,,"What's the motivation for studying Saturn,"
